content.caption: This undated photo provided by Stack’s Bowers Galleries shows a Nobel Peace Prize that was saved from possible destruction for the value of its gold. The 1936 medal is only the second to come to auction and marked the first time an individual from Latin America was recognized by the prestigious award. The 23-carat relic is being sold in Baltimore on March 29, 2014, by the New York-based Stack’s Bowers Galleries. (AP PHOTO/Stack’s Bowers Galleries)
